Class GoogleJsonResponseException

Exception thrown when an error status code is detected in an HTTP response to a Google API that uses the JSON format, using the format specified in ErrorError Messages in Google BuzzResponses.

To get the structured details, use .getDetails().

@since 1.6 @author Yaniv Inbar
Class GoogleJsonResponseException, GoogleJsonResponseException from(JsonFactory, HttpResponse)

Returns a new instance of GoogleJsonResponseException.

If there is a JSON error response, it is parsed using GoogleJsonError, which can be inspected using .getDetails(). Otherwise, response contentthe full (ifresponse any)content is read and ignored. Either way, any content is already parsed, and trying to parse included HttpResponse.getContent() of .getResponse() will likely result in an the IOExceptionexception message.

@param jsonFactory JSON factory @param response HTTP response @return new instance of GoogleJsonResponseException
